CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 23, 1960, pg. 1 reads: "Auto Parade - As a prelude to the "Rebels" rally at Westinghouse High School auditorium, the "Rebels" staged an 108 car torchlight parade..."
TitMainTitle: Four women and man in two toned car, with "7th District" sign, during torchlight parade for 13th Ward "Rebels" rally
